Geometric Brownian motion

library(tidyverse)
library(rstan)
library(loo)
options(mc.cores=4)
rstan_options(auto_write=TRUE)
source("helper.R")
set.seed(1)

In this notebook, we perform inference for geometric Brownian motion, which has an SDE:

\[\begin{equation} dX(t) = \theta X(t) + \kappa X(t) dW(t) \end{equation}\]

This SDE has a the following probability density, which allows us to exactly simulate from the process:

\[\begin{equation} X(t+\delta t) | X(t) \sim \text{log-normal}(\log X(t) + (\theta - 0.5\kappa^2)\delta_t, \kappa \sqrt{t}) \end{equation}\]

simulate_gbm <- function(X_0, T, N, theta, kappa) {
  delta_t <- T / N
  X <- vector(length = (N + 1))
  X[1] <- X_0
  for(i in 1:N) {
    X[i + 1] <- rlnorm(1, log(X[i]) + (theta - 0.5 * kappa^2) * delta_t, kappa * sqrt(delta_t))
  }
  X
}

T <- 10
N <- 500
X_0 <- 1
theta <- 0.5
kappa <- 0.5
X <- simulate_gbm(X_0, T, N, theta, kappa)
t <- seq(0, T, T/N)

# plot
df <- tibble(t, X)
df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=t, y=X)) +
  geom_line()

We now add some noise to the data.

Approximate inference

```r
model_approx <- stan_model(\stan/gbm_approx.stan\)

# fit model with many different Zs
stan_data <- list(
    nobs=nrow(df),
    t=df$t,
    Y=df$Y,
    X_0=X_0,
    T=T,
    kappa_mean=0,
    kappa_width=10)
init_fn_list <- list(
  theta=theta,
  kappa=kappa,
  sigma_n=1)
Nzs <- c(2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256)
lfits <- vector(mode=\list\, length = length(Nzs))
for(i in seq_along(Nzs)) {
  print(paste0(\i = \, i))
  lfits[[i]] <- fit_model_any_z(
    Nzs[i], model_approx, init_fn_list, stan_data,
    iters=2000)
}

```r
extract_param <- function(param_name, fit) {
  rstan::extract(fit, param_name)[[1]]
}
Ns <- c(Nzs)
params <- c(\theta\, \kappa\, \sigma_n\)
k <- 1
for(j in seq_along(params)) {
  for(i in seq_along(lfits)) {
    draws <- extract_param(params[j], lfits[[i]])
    temp <- tibble(value=draws,
                   iter=seq_along(draws),
                   N=Ns[i],
                   param=params[j])
    if(k == 1)
      big_df <- temp
    else
      big_df <- big_df %>% bind_rows(temp)
    k <- k + 1
  }
}
big_df <- big_df %>% 
  mutate(param=as.factor(param)) %>% 
  mutate(param=fct_relevel(param, params))
saveRDS(big_df, \../data/processed/gbm_approx_fits.rds\)

params <- c(\theta\, \kappa\, \sigma\)
big_df <- readRDS(\../data/processed/gbm_approx_fits.rds\) %>% 
  mutate(param=as.character(param)) %>% 
  mutate(param=if_else(param==\sigma_n\, \sigma\, param)) %>% 
  mutate(param=fct_relevel(param, params))

short_df <- tribble(
  ~param, ~value,
  \theta\, theta,
  \kappa\, kappa,
  \sigma\, sigma_n
) %>% 
  mutate(param=as.factor(param)) %>% 
  mutate(param=fct_relevel(param, params))

g <- ggplot(big_df,
       aes(x=value, colour=as.factor(N))) +
  stat_density(geom=\line\, position=\identity\,
               data=big_df %>% filter(N != \true\) %>%
                 mutate(N=as.numeric(as.character(N)))) +
  scale_color_brewer(\N\, palette = \Spectral\) +
   geom_vline(data=short_df, aes(xintercept=value), linetype=2) +
  facet_wrap(~param, scales=\free\,
             labeller = label_parsed)
ggsave(\../figures/gbm_fits_vs_actual.pdf\, g,
       width = 10, height = 6)

Extract log-likelihoods to perform model comparison

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubG9vcyA8LSB2ZWN0b3IobGVuZ3RoID0gbGVuZ3RoKGxmaXRzKSwgbW9kZT1cXGxpc3RcXClcbmZvcihpIGluIHNlcV9hbG9uZyhsb29zKSkge1xuICBsb2dfbGlrZSA8LSBleHRyYWN0X2xvZ19saWsobGZpdHNbW2ldXSwgXFxsb2dsaWtlbGlob29kXFwpXG4gIGxvb3NbW2ldXSA8LSBsb28obG9nX2xpa2UpXG59XG5zYXZlUkRTKGxvb3MsIFxcLi4vZGF0YS9wcm9jZXNzZWQvZ2JtX2xvb3MucmRzXFwpXG5sb29fY29tcGFyZShsb29zKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
loos <- vector(length = length(lfits), mode=\list\)
for(i in seq_along(loos)) {
  log_like <- extract_log_lik(lfits[[i]], \loglikelihood\)
  loos[[i]] <- loo(log_like)
}
saveRDS(loos, \../data/processed/gbm_loos.rds\)
loo_compare(loos)

Check convergence

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucmhhdHMgPC0gdmVjdG9yKGxlbmd0aD1sZW5ndGgobGZpdHMpKVxuZXNzcyA8LSB2ZWN0b3IobGVuZ3RoPWxlbmd0aChsZml0cykpXG5mb3IoaSBpbiBzZXFfYWxvbmcobGZpdHMpKSB7XG4gIHN1bV9kZiA8LSBwb3N0ZXJpb3I6OnN1bW1hcmlzZV9kcmF3cyhsZml0c1tbaV1dKVxuICByaGF0c1tpXSA8LSBzdW0oc3VtX2RmJHJoYXQgPiAxLjAxLCBuYS5ybSA9IFQpXG4gIGJ1bGtfZXNzIDwtIHN1bShzdW1fZGYkZXNzX2J1bGsgPCA0MDAsIG5hLnJtID0gVClcbiAgdGFpbF9lc3MgPC0gc3VtKHN1bV9kZiRlc3NfdGFpbCA8IDQwMCwgbmEucm0gPSBUKVxuICBlc3NzW2ldIDwtIGJ1bGtfZXNzICsgdGFpbF9lc3Ncbn1cbmNvbnZfZGYgPC0gdGliYmxlKFxuICByaGF0PXJoYXRzLCBlc3M9ZXNzc1xuKVxuc2F2ZVJEUyhjb252X2RmLCBcXC4uL2RhdGEvcHJvY2Vzc2VkL2dibV9jb252ZXJnZW5jZV9kaWFncy5yZHNcXClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
rhats <- vector(length=length(lfits))
esss <- vector(length=length(lfits))
for(i in seq_along(lfits)) {
  sum_df <- posterior::summarise_draws(lfits[[i]])
  rhats[i] <- sum(sum_df$rhat > 1.01, na.rm = T)
  bulk_ess <- sum(sum_df$ess_bulk < 400, na.rm = T)
  tail_ess <- sum(sum_df$ess_tail < 400, na.rm = T)
  esss[i] <- bulk_ess + tail_ess
}
conv_df <- tibble(
  rhat=rhats, ess=esss
)
saveRDS(conv_df, \../data/processed/gbm_convergence_diags.rds\)

AIC scans for different realisations

aic_scan <- function(df, Nzs) {
  lopts <- vector(mode="list", length = length(Nzs))
  stan_data <- list(
    nobs=nrow(df),
    t=df$t,
    Y=df$Y,
    X_0=X_0,
    T=T,
    kappa_mean=0,
    kappa_width=10)
  
  for(i in seq_along(Nzs)) {
    print(paste0("i = ", i))
    lopts[[i]] <- optimise_model_any_z(
      Nzs[i], model_approx, init_fn_list, stan_data)
  }
  lvals <- vector(length = length(Nzs))
for(i in seq_along(lvals))
  lvals[i] <- 2 * (Nzs[i] + N_theta) - 2 * lopts[[i]]$value
  lvals
}

simulate_dataset <- function(theta=0.5, kappa=0.5, sigma_n=0.1) {
  T <- 10
  N <- 500
  X_0 <- 1
  X <- simulate_gbm(X_0, T, N, theta, kappa)
  t <- seq(0, T, T/N)
  df <- tibble(t, X)
  Y <- rlnorm(length(X), log(X) - 0.5 * sigma_n^2, sigma_n)
  df <- df %>% 
    mutate(Y=Y)
  df %>% 
    filter(t > 0)
}

Nzs <- c(2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256)
Nrepeats <- 5
m_aics <- matrix(nrow = length(Nzs),
                 ncol = Nrepeats)
for(i in 1:Nrepeats) {
  print(paste0("iter = ", i))
  df_temp <- simulate_dataset()
  m_aics[, i] <- aic_scan(df_temp, Nzs)
}

m_aics <- as.data.frame(m_aics)
colnames(m_aics) <- 1:Nrepeats
m_aics <- m_aics %>% 
  mutate(N=Nzs)
saveRDS(m_aics, "../data/processed/gbm_aics_different_samples.rds")
m_aics <- readRDS("../data/processed/gbm_aics_different_samples.rds")
g <- m_aics %>%
  pivot_longer(-N) %>%
  mutate(name=as.factor(name)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=N, y=value, colour=name)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_x_log10(breaks=Nzs) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  ylab("AIC")
g
ggsave("../figures/gbm_aics_repeats.pdf", g,
       width = 8, height = 4)
apply(m_aics, 2, which.min)

# Use variable transformation to convert system to one where higher harmonics play a lesser role

Use the variable transformation: $S(t) = \log X(t)$ and apply Ito's lemma:

\begin{equation}
dS(t) = (\theta - 1/2 \kappa^2)dt + \kappa dW(t)
\end{equation}

On this transformed scale, the measurement process is of the form:

\begin{equation}
V(t) \sim \text{normal}(S(t) - 1/2\sigma^2, \sigma)
\end{equation}


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuZGYgPC0gcmVhZFJEUyhcIi4uL2RhdGEvcHJvY2Vzc2VkL2dibV9zaW11bGF0aW9uLnJkc1wiKSAlPiUgXG4gIGZpbHRlcih0ID4gMCkgJT4lIFxuICBtdXRhdGUoUz1sb2coWCkpICU+JSBcbiAgbXV0YXRlKFY9bG9nKFkpKSAlPiUgXG4gIG11dGF0ZShtdT0odGhldGEgLSBrYXBwYV4yKSAqIHQpXG5cbm1vZGVsX2FwcHJveCA8LSBzdGFuX21vZGVsKFwic3Rhbi9nYm1fYXBwcm94X3RyYW5zZm9ybS5zdGFuXCIpXG4jIGZpdCBtb2RlbCB3aXRoIG1hbnkgZGlmZmVyZW50IFpzXG5zdGFuX2RhdGEgPC0gbGlzdChcbiAgICBub2JzPW5yb3coZGYpLFxuICAgIHQ9ZGYkdCxcbiAgICBWPWRmJFYsXG4gICAgU18wPWxvZyhYXzApLFxuICAgIFQ9VCxcbiAgICBrYXBwYV9tZWFuPTAsXG4gICAga2FwcGFfd2lkdGg9MTApXG5pbml0X2ZuX2xpc3QgPC0gbGlzdChcbiAgdGhldGE9dGhldGEsXG4gIGthcHBhPWthcHBhLFxuICBzaWdtYV9uPTEpXG5cbmZpdCA8LSBmaXRfbW9kZWxfYW55X3ooXG4gICAgMzIsIG1vZGVsX2FwcHJveCwgaW5pdF9mbl9saXN0LCBzdGFuX2RhdGEsXG4gICAgaXRlcnM9MTAwLHJlZnJlc2hfdmFsID0gMTApXG5wcmludChmaXQsIGMoXCJrYXBwYVwiLCBcInRoZXRhXCIsIFwic2lnbWFfblwiKSlcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
df <- readRDS("../data/processed/gbm_simulation.rds") %>% 
  filter(t > 0) %>% 
  mutate(S=log(X)) %>% 
  mutate(V=log(Y)) %>% 
  mutate(mu=(theta - kappa^2) * t)

model_approx <- stan_model("stan/gbm_approx_transform.stan")
# fit model with many different Zs
stan_data <- list(
    nobs=nrow(df),
    t=df$t,
    V=df$V,
    S_0=log(X_0),
    T=T,
    kappa_mean=0,
    kappa_width=10)
init_fn_list <- list(
  theta=theta,
  kappa=kappa,
  sigma_n=1)

fit <- fit_model_any_z(
    32, model_approx, init_fn_list, stan_data,
    iters=100,refresh_val = 10)
print(fit, c("kappa", "theta", "sigma_n"))
T <- 10
theta <- 1
kappa <- 1
X1 <- simulate_gbm(X_0, T, N, theta, kappa)
Y1 <- rlnorm(length(X1), log(X1) - 0.5 * sigma_n^2, sigma_n)
df <- df %>% 
  mutate(X=X1[-1]) %>% 
  mutate(t=seq(0.0, T, T / N)[-1]) %>% 
  mutate(Y=Y1[-1]) %>% 
  filter(t > 0) %>% 
  mutate(S=log(X1[-1])) %>% 
  mutate(V=log(Y)) %>% 
  mutate(mu=(theta - 0.5 * kappa^2) * t)
stan_data <- list(
    nobs=nrow(df),
    t=df$t,
    V=df$V,
    S_0=log(X_0),
    T=T,
    kappa_mean=0,
    kappa_width=10)

Nzs <- c(2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64)
lopts <- vector(mode="list", length = length(Nzs))
for(i in seq_along(Nzs)) {
  print(paste0("i = ", i))
  lopts[[i]] <- optimise_model_any_z(
    Nzs[i], model_approx, init_fn_list, stan_data)
}

  opt <- lopts[[i]]
  temp_df <- tibble(t=df$t,
                    log_X=opt$par$X_sim[, 1],
                    N=Nzs[i])
  if(i == 1)
    big_df <- temp_df
  else
    big_df <- big_df %>% bind_rows(temp_df)

       aes(x=t, y=log_X)) +
  geom_line() +

            aes(colour=as.factor(N)))
